                        <td>
                        
                            <h1><a href="https://www.theigc.org/funding/call-for-proposals" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">New </a><a href="https://www.theigc.org/funding/call-for-proposals" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">IGC call for proposals will open in September</a></h1>

<p><br/>
The IGC will be opening a call for proposals on 29 September 2023 for research projects relevant to <strong>promoting sustainable growth in developing countries</strong>. We accept proposals from any researcher, including PhD students and researchers based in developing countries.<br/>
<br/>
We strongly encourage applicants to conduct research in one of our <a href="https://www.theigc.org/where-we-work" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">10 partner countries</a>. Engaging with our country teams comes with advantages - access to local research partners, datasets, and dedicated support for policy engagement. <strong>If you wish to apply, please get in touch with the relevant IGC country office as early as possible to discuss your proposal before submitting it</strong>. Receiving feedback on your proposal will ensure it is well-aligned with policy priorities.<br/>
<br/>
This year, we are offering<strong> </strong><strong>full research grants</strong> for research proposals at a mature level of development and with a well-defined research question, and <strong>small research grants </strong>for pilot studies and exploratory research.<br/>
<br/>
The call opens on 29 September, with a submission deadline on 12 November. Application decisions will be made in February 2024, and applicants will be notified shortly thereafter.<br/>
<br/>
Please check the IGC website closer to the date for updated guidelines and instructions on how to apply, and stay tuned for more information.</p>

